race.comment: SPINHOF (2) lifted strongly to score by half a length at the most recent appearance over 1200m at St Arnaud at the second run this prep. Finds the right race to make it two on the trot. METEORITE (3) missed the frame when resuming last start over 1000m at Warrnambool but wasn't all that far from the winner. Won't find this as tough. MAJESTIC DIVA (13) has a terrible winning strike-rate - 2 wins from 54 starts - but got within 1.3 lengths of SPINHOF last start and that looks the right form for this race. IN THE SUN (12) has been out of the winner's list for a long time, last start finishing fourth at Warrnambool over 1400m after being prominent until the final stages. ZOULAR (1) showed little early speed last start and failed to come on in the straight when tenth, beaten 7 lengths, over 1300m at Penola. Well placed and there is no reason he cannot find winning ways.
